Wale Oyewale, Ibadan THE family of the late politician, Dr Olapade Adegoro, has confirmed his death. The widow of the former presidential candidate, Mrs. Wonuola Olapade-Agoro, confirmed his death in an exclusive interview, with The PUNCH on Sunday. She explained that her husband passed on in the early hours of Sunday after an ailment, which lasted three weeks. [READ ALSO] 2023: Will Tinubu fight or run away? Wonuola, while confirming his demise, said, “It is very true; Baba has left. He has left us.” Also, a son of the deceased, Adebo, said, “It happened around 2.15am on Sunday. He had been sick; he had been on hospital management for about three weeks. He passed on at the specialist hospital where he was receiving treatment. He was 77.” Copyright PUNCH.
